TARGET: "SEO professionals, content creators, digital marketers"
TYPE: "Comprehensive Guide"

REQUIREMENTS:
- 2500+ words
- 7+ authoritative sources (academic, industry reports)
- 5+ expert quotes (SEO industry leaders)
- 3+ case studies with real metrics
- 7+ step-by-step implementation guides
- 10+ FAQ with schema
- All content must be REAL, not placeholder
- Must score 100/100 when checked

START WRITING NOW. Do not ask questions. Fill every placeholder with actual content.
```

---

## üí° TIPS FOR BEST RESULTS

1. **Be Specific About Topic**
   - Good: "How to Implement GRAAF Framework for B2B SaaS"
   - Bad: "SEO tips"

2. **Specify Content Type**
   - Guide (comprehensive how-to)
   - Case Study (real results)
   - Tutorial (step-by-step)
   - Comparison (X vs Y)

3. **Give AI Context**
   - Target audience
   - Industry/niche
   - Desired outcome
   - Tone preference

4. **Request Verification**
   - "Verify all 100/100 requirements met"
   - "Check schema markup validity"
   - "Confirm 7+ internal links present"

---

## üö® COMMON AI MISTAKES TO AVOID

### **Mistake 1: Leaving Placeholders**
```html
‚ùå <title>[PRIMARY KEYWORD]: [BENEFIT]</title>
‚úÖ <title>GRAAF Framework: 5-Pillar SEO Guide (2025)</title>
```

### **Mistake 2: Generic Expert Quotes**
```html
‚ùå "Content quality matters" - John Smith, SEO Expert
‚úÖ "Content frameworks that systematically address all quality dimensions 
    outperform tactical optimizations by 340%" - Dr. Sarah Chen, PhD in 
    Information Retrieval from MIT, Senior Research Scientist at Google
```

### **Mistake 3: Vague Case Studies**
```html
‚ùå Company X improved their traffic
‚úÖ TechVentures Inc. (B2B SaaS): Traffic 6,992 ‚Üí 27,880 (+299%), 
    90 days, verified via Google Analytics 4
```

### **Mistake 4: Missing Schema**
```html
‚ùå No schema markup at all
‚úÖ All 3 schema types (Article, FAQ, Breadcrumb) implemented and validated
```

